---
title: Cheesy Beef Tostadas with Green Pepper, Tomato Salsa, and Hot Sauce Crema
description: We love a good ground-beef taco, but you don’t need us to tell you how to make one—there are kits for that. Instead, we’re here to show you how to take Tex-Mex night to the next level. So enter the tostada, featuring a flat tortilla baked until crisp, with lots of surface area for piling it on. Thankfully, there are plenty of toppings in this recipe, and not just warmly spiced ground beef—there’s also green pepper, tomato salsa, and a spicy sour cream.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5d6e7de4267dd400115aadf6-f0c6275b.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/cheesy-beef-tostadas-5d6e7de4267dd400115aadf6-355e27b6.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 950 kcal
  fat: 54 g
  saturated fat: 24 g
  carbohydrates: 52 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1920 mg
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: Mexican
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cheesy-beef-tostadas-5d6e7de4267dd400115aadf6
time required: 40 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Dice @Roma tomato{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce} leaves and stems. Quarter @lime{1}. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}. Halve and peel @yellow onion{1}; thinly slice one half. Finely chop remaining onion until you have 2 TBSP.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine tomato, cilantro, chopped onion, juice from half the lime, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}. In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and as much @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} as you like. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @chili powder{1%teaspoon}, and a few big pinches of salt. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{4-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in step 4).

Once beef is browned, add green pepper, sliced onion, and a pinch of salt to pan. Cook, stirring, until veggies are tender and beef is cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}. Add @beef stock concentrate{1} and 1/4 cup water (1/2 cup water for 4 servings). Simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt; remove pan from heat and set aside.

Drizzle @flour tortillas{6} with 1 TBSP olive oil (2 TBSP for 4 servings); brush or rub to coat all over. Arrange on a #baking sheet{} in a single layer (divide between 2 baking sheets for 4). Gently prick each tortilla in a few places with a #fork{}. Bake on top rack, flipping halfway through, until lightly golden, ~{4-5%minutes} per side.

> For 4 servings, bake on top and middle racks; flip and swap baking sheet positions halfway through cooking.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Divide tortillas between plates; evenly sprinkle with @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}. Top with beef mixture, salsa, and crema. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.